Mons mr Jean Batp. Masson
j'espere ne bon arrivement a mons. celle cy ne serura que pour vous adviser que
m. marchandise est partij d'Jeij hier dans un ballotte 18M consigne a mad. de vos
suivante la facture jey enclu, les noirs de 3Æ’ & le bancke de 48 pattar serons accomode
ensamble avecq les Bays & drap sealatt selon vd. ad, pour vous envoyer, vous assaret
que en tous occasions, en les quelles je vous pou rendre service que je ne marquenaoy

dat vant getouwe kompt laet dat iouwe oft ongeevolt kemen

Eoen mr. itt. Lobb & Comp
I have before mee boath yd of 8 & 11h past, John Ewinges is well arrived, so shall exspect the
22 cloth & 8 Â£ 24 yd. serges p m. Wills, & in case you can serovide time enough for wills 20 serges
or 30, assorted in cullours as 2 N.1 butt in prijses under 40 a 41 Æ’ a 5 us 22 yd, so pray do
yd endeavour to send mee one bale mone, I have nott yett receaved the goods, & I doubt our
our customens will not come to so high prijse, & there fore shall want some of lesser pryse
I have about Â£100- neady in handes of m mill sealy of yd towne which I'll remitt you
the next post, because I want to know the nesd soma other wise I should remitt now, so you
maij depend hereon whilst I remaine
C4d
pen mr. William Sealy
On the 21th past have advised you the needfull, sence is John lwings well arrived, & I supose the
clovenseed loaden on his board by this time there beeng in all 15 op heads for you, containing
as by the inclosed noate you may see, butt because I have not yett the charges att Gant
Bruges, can not send you a perseet invoyce, which you shall have next, I shall want
the valeu in epon, & there fore desire you to pay itt there owing some mony to mr. Will. Lobble
whres condition I could wish you would be pleased to advise mee
a 4d
London m. Geonge Cole
I have non of yd. to answer, so this onely for advises that I have bought 1o opheads of
qune good, & of the vere best nuw cloverseed that was to be found, which I supose is shipt by this
time att Bruger aboard John Ewings, whe is there now, the contents you have here inclosed, &
because I want the charges att Bridges of shipping can not send you a perseet invoyce before
next post, the valeuw shall come good to the acctt of the estate of JV., & then there will be not
much resting, which shall be remitted you also to make an end of itt. on the 14th past wrott
you of some mony to pay m. Hobb of Eoon, for which att present shall have no occasion
haveing remitted him the needfull
C 4d
London mm. Jeuniy Collier
